definition: most likely/mostly (in 8 or 9 cases out of 10)/vast majority
to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be

sentences.english: If you talk to ten successful adults, nine of them will have totally unbelievable stories like this.
sentences.chinese: 那写成功人士十有八九都有这样让人难以置信的经历。

sentences.english: Nine chances out of ten we'd both wind up in a concentration camp.
sentences.chinese: 我们俩十有八九会被抓进集中营。

sentences.english: Nine times out of ten, the side with the best surface roots will be the front.
sentences.chinese: 十有八九，长有最好地面根的一面应确立为观赏面。

sentences.english: All too often, businesses are undercapitalized and forced to survive hand to mouth.
sentences.chinese: 企业十有八九资金不足，被迫勉强维持着生存。

sentences.english: You know that nine out of ten con-men end up spending empty bitter lives as chiropractors ?
sentences.chinese: 骗子的下场十有八九只能靠按摩过日子。

sentences.english: Eight or nine of the ten victims, labeled lackeys, were poor people.
sentences.chinese: 十有八九是我们俩最终都进集中营。

sentences.english: Why, the doctor told me this morning that your chances for getting well real soon were ten to one!
sentences.chinese: 对了，大夫上午跟我说，你的病十有八九就快好了。

sentences.english: By my experiences, nine out of ten she committed suicide by cutting wrist.
sentences.chinese: 年轻的警察说，“我看，十有八九是割腕自杀。

definition: most likely/mostly (in 8 or 9 cases out of 10)/vast majority
to be bound to/to be sure to
to conclude/to determine/to come to a judgment
needless to say/it goes without saying
hard to say/can't guarantee/difficult to protect/difficult to preserve
